Paul,

I suggest that you folks should consider producing an official
specification of how a domain server's database should distinguish
between different internet addresses.  As well as making the
primary/secondary distinction explicit, you might consider ways of
including geographical or network topology information explicit in the
database to improve efficiency.  I think that attempting to optimize
performance in this way is a very interesting issue.  It will be a very
challenging problem to figure out what sorts of information might be
available to improve performance, and how it is feasible to use this
information.	

I think people are going to come up with a lot of ugly, incompatible,
ad-hoc schemes if no standard is spelled out.

Peter
